Since $Y_j = X_j$ for $j \neq i$ and $Y_i = -X_i$, we need to analyze how this affects the product. For an odd permutation $I$, the product $\prod_{k=1}^m \langle X_{I_k}, X_{I_{m+1-k}} \rangle$ involves an odd number of terms where $X_i$ appears. When we replace $X_i$ with $-X_i$, the product becomes $(-1)^{\text{odd}} \cdot \prod_{k=1}^m \langle X_{I_k}, X_{I_{m+1-k}} \rangle = -\prod_{k=1}^m \langle X_{I_k}, X_{I_{m+1-k}} \rangle$.

